Installation

https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/

# 1. Select OS
- Mac (Intel or Apple Silicon)
- Linux
- Windows

# 2. Select Package (Recommended: conda or pip)
conda
pip

# 3. Select Language
Python (Recommended 3.8 - 3.11)

# 4. Select Compute Platform
- CUDA 11.8 / 12.1 (for NVIDIA GPUs)
- MPS (Metal Performance Shaders) is built-in for MacOS 12.3+
- CPU (if no GPU)

# Installation Examples:

# --- MacOS (Apple Silicon & Intel) ---
# MPS acceleration is available on MacOS 12.3+
conda install pytorch torchvision torchaudio -c pytorch

# --- Linux / Windows (NVIDIA GPU) ---
# Example for CUDA 11.8
conda install pytorch torchvision torchaudio pytorch-cuda=11.8 -c pytorch -c nvidia

# --- CPU Only ---
conda install pytorch torchvision torchaudio cpuonly -c pytorch

# Verification:
import torch
x = torch.rand(5, 3)
print(x)

# Check for GPU availability
print(f"CUDA available: {torch.cuda.is_available()}")
print(f"MPS available: {torch.backends.mps.is_available()}") # MacOS

if torch.cuda.is_available():
    print(f"Current CUDA device: {torch.cuda.current_device()}")
    print(f"Device name: {torch.cuda.get_device_name(0)}")